# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# agent-seal .dockerignore — Multi-stage Docker build exclusion
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Prevents host artifacts from bloating the Docker build context.
# Sent to Docker daemon on `docker build` (and `docker compose build`).
# Design: docs/architecture-v1.md §5.3 (deployment architecture)
#
# Key stages that use build context:
#   spa-builder — COPY spa/* (package.json, lock, source)
#   builder     — COPY setup.py README.md, then COPY . .
#   production  — COPY docker-entrypoint.sh (direct from context)
#
# INCLUSION RULE: Only exclude files that are NOT needed by any build stage.
# docker-entrypoint.sh is explicitly needed by the production stage.

# ═══════════════════ Docker self-references ═══════════════════
# Dockerfile is read by the daemon separately; no need in context.
# docker-compose files are for orchestration, not image content.
Dockerfile
docker-compose*.yml
docker-compose.override.yml

# ═══════════════════ Version control ═════════════════════════
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/

# ═══════════════════ Python bytecode & caches ═══════════════
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo

# ═══════════════════ Python build artifacts ═════════════════
# Generated by `python setup.py sdist` / `pip install -e .`
# These are recreated during the Docker build; copying host versions
# causes stale metadata and platform mismatches.
*.egg-info/
*.egg
.eggs/
dist/
build/

# ═══════════════════ Virtual environments ═══════════════════
# Host .venv/ must NOT leak into the image — it's the wrong Python,
# wrong platform, and may contain native extensions compiled for Windows.
.venv*/
venv*/
env/

# ═══════════════════ Testing (NOT needed at runtime) ═══════
# Tests and test harnesses are local dev tools. The production image
# does not run pytest.
tests/
test/
test.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
.pytest_cache/
.benchmarks/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# ═══════════════════ One-off verification / dev scripts ═════
_verify_trail_storage_delegation.py
final_verify.py
verify_models.py
benchmark_phase44.py
_check_deps.py
_hello2.py

# ═══════════════════ Trash / stale artifacts ════════════════
_trash/

# ═══════════════════ Audit logs (runtime, not build-time) ═══
audit_logs/

# ═══════════════════ Deployment configs (not in image) ══════
# Helm charts and infrastructure configs are applied externally.
# nginx configs are volume-mounted by docker-compose at runtime.
deploy/
nginx/

# ═══════════════════ Documentation (not needed at runtime) ══
docs/

# ═══════════════════ Examples (not needed at runtime) ═══════
examples/

# ═══════════════════ Node modules (SPA) ═════════════════════
# The Dockerfile's spa-builder stage runs `npm ci` to install
# dependencies fresh from package-lock.json. Host node_modules/
# should never be copied into the build context.
spa/node_modules/

# ═══════════════════ Project metadata (not needed at runtime)
# setup.py, pyproject.toml, README.md, and requirements.txt are
# needed by the builder stage — do NOT exclude them.
# These files are reference-only and not read by the application.
CHANGELOG.md
RELEASE-v1.0.md
LICENSE
MANIFEST.in
requirements-dev.txt

# ═══════════════════ Environment secrets ════════════════════
# .env files contain secrets and dev overrides. Production
# config is injected via docker-compose environment: keys.
.env
.env.local
.env.production

# ═══════════════════ IDE / Editor ═══════════════════════════
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ═══════════════════ OS junk ════════════════════════════════
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ═══════════════════ Temp / stale test dirs ═════════════════
# These directories appear to be test artifacts from local runs.
some_dir/
some_uri/
